 <H1>Learning from complex stimuli</H1> 
 <P><UL>
<LI><H2>Photographs of people doing something to a balloon
</H2>
<UL>
<LI>Action: Stretching the balloon or dipping the balloon in water
<LI>Color: Yellow or Purple
<LI>Age of Person: Adult or Child
<LI>(Size of Balloon: Large or Small)
</UL></UL><UL>
<LI><H2>Standard Concept Acquisition Experiment
</H2>
<UL>
1.	Show subject photograph
<BR><BR>2.	Ask for category label (Alpha or not Alpha)
<BR>3.	Give correct answer
<BR>4.	Stop when six correct in a row
</UL></UL><UL>
<LI><H2>Prediction from Classic Concept Learning:
</H2>
<UL>
<LI>Disjunctive rules harder to learn than conjunctive</UL></UL></P>
